
[1]sparingly

   SPA'RINGLY, adv.

   1. Not abundantly.

   2. Frugally; parsimoniously; not lavishly. High titles of honor were in
   the king's minority sparingly granted, because dignity then waited on
   desert. Commend but sparingly whom thou dost love.

   3. Abstinently; moderately. Christians are obliged to taste even the
   innocent pleasures of life but sparingly.

   4. Seldom; not frequently. The morality of a grave sentence, affected
   by Lucan, is more sparingly used by Virgil.

   5. Cautiously; tenderly.
